You should really try using natural/organic skincare. Not only is it better for the environment, but it's better for your health in the long term. There are a lot of misconceptions about natural brands and products because of the lack of real information that is being presented to the public. Natural ingredients are incredible and can be extremely powerful and effective if used correctly and safely. There's a reason why they've existed for centuries in alternative medicine etc. The problem with using synthetically made products (which accounts for the majority of products in the industry), is that in the short term they may be safe to use, but there is scientific evidence that in the long term a lot of the ingredients can be carcinogenic (having the potential to cause cancer). The reason why labs make synthetic versions of natural ingredients is because the molecules in the natural ingredient is often too large to penetrate the skin to a deeper level, hence it may not be as effective. And most people are looking for a quick fix. So in order to compensate for this, they create a synthetic version where the molecules are much smaller. However, because they are smaller it means that they are so small they actually enter the bloodstream. Now imagine spending 50 years putting these synthetic chemicals on your face and it being absorbed into your blood... I know that ever since I started using natural skincare, the thought of that freaks me out.

*I can speak about these things because my mum is a qualified natural skincare formulator and has spent the past 2 years researching natural ingredients and the science behind how the skin works etc.
**I would also avoid using Malin & Goetz because some of their products are extremely unstable and unsafe. My mum used one of their products and now has a permanent scar on her face. There were a tonne of negative reviews about this particular product that they 'conveniently' neglected to show on their website and the product was never recalled. It's disgusting how far a company will go just to make more money, even if it's putting people's health at risk.
***Try and avoid using products that have fragrance or alcohol in them (quite a few of the products you're using) because alcohol can really dry out your skin and synthetic fragrance is an irritant. The reason your skin is going red when you use the toner is probably because some of the ingredients in it are irritating your skin.

Hope this informed someone x If you want to know more, let me know! I'm happy to share the information.
